The problem requires finding the employee with the longest working time among n employees. We can solve this problem by iterating through the logs array once and updating the result variable whenever we find a new maximum value. Since the logs array is sorted in ascending order, we can directly compare the first element of each subarray to the current result. This solution has a time complexity of O(n) and a space complexity of O(1), making it efficient for large input sizes.

